// JavaScript Can Change HTML Content! One of many JavaScript HTML methods is "getElementById()".

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>Look what I can do!</h2>

<p id="demo">I can change HTML content. ^„ÖÅ^</p>

<button type="button" onclick='document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "It changed! Its really easy" '>Click Me!</button>

</body>
</html>

// JavaScript Can Change HTML Attribute Values. In this case JavaScript changes the value of the src (source) attribute of an image.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>What Can JavaScript Do?</h2>

<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='pic_bulbon.gif'">Turn on the light</button>

<img id="myImage" src="pic_bulboff.gif" style="width:100px">

<button onclick="document.getElementById('myImage').src='pic_bulboff.gif'">Turn off the light</button>

</body>
</html>
